body:
After upgrading to **Cordova 9.0.0 & Cordova-Android 8.0.0** I also reproducibly experienced a similar problem were the otherwise correctly generated Android Manifest file under **platforms/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml** was corrupted during **'cordova prepare'** phase. The actual changes (manifest "corruption") consisted in removing several **uses-permission** and **uses-features** tags from the initially correct manifest:
```xml 
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.REQUEST_INSTALL_PACKAGES" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.CAMERA" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FLASHLIGHT" />
    <uses-feature android:name="android.hardware.camera" android:required="true" />
```
After digging a lot to find a solution to avoid this annoying behavior, I ended up with a final work-around where I used a Cordova hook for **before_prepare** & **after_prepare** that will backup & restore the correct manifest. 

Until an official fix/update will be provided, here is the hook that I've implemented, hoping to be useful for others encountering this bug. 
Please note the hook (to be removed when the bug is fixed!) is implemented into a single JavaScript file (**hooks/android_manifest_fixer.js**) covering both events being registered under **config.xml** as follows:

```xml
<hook type="before_prepare" src="hooks/android_manifest_fixer.js"/>
<hook type="after_prepare" src="hooks/android_manifest_fixer.js"/>
```

Below I included the relevant **hooks/android_manifest_fixer.js** JavaScript code that will backup & restore the manifest where the new created files (**AndroidManifest.xml.good** + **AndroidManifest.xml.bad**) are saved directly under **app** root folder (outside the **src** path) to avoid being included into Android app build processing.

```java
"use strict";

/* eslint-env node */
var fs = require("fs"),
	utils = require("./utils"),
	colors = utils.colors,
	log = utils.log;

// hook function
function hook(context) {
	var manifestPath = "./platforms/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml",
		manifestPathGood = "./platforms/android/app/AndroidManifest.xml.good",
		read = function(file) {
			return fs.readFileSync(file, "utf8");
		},
		write = function(file, str) {
			return fs.writeFileSync(file, str, "utf8");
		},
		copy = function(source, dest) {
			write(dest, read(source));
		};
	if (context.hook === "before_prepare") {
		// backup the manifest
		log("Backup 'AndroidManifest.xml' as " + colors.yellow(manifestPathGood));
		copy(manifestPath, manifestPathGood);
	} else if (context.hook === "after_prepare") {
		var manifestText = read(manifestPath),
			manifestTextGood = read(manifestPathGood),
			manifestPathBad = "./platforms/android/app/AndroidManifest.xml.bad";
		// check if the the manifest was changed during preparation
		if (manifestText !== manifestTextGood) {
			log("Save corrupted 'AndroidManifest.xml' under " +	colors.yellow(manifestPathBad));
			write(manifestPathBad, manifestText);
			log("Restore 'AndroidManifest.xml' from " + colors.yellow(manifestPathGood));
			write(manifestPath, manifestTextGood);
		} else {
			log("The AndroidManifest.xml is not modified during prepare " + colors.red(" -> The 'android_manifest_fixer' hook is NOT needed anymore !"));
		}
	}
}

// export hook function
module.exports = hook;
```

